-- Obama’s Convention Speech to Be ‘Aspirational,’ ‘Pragmatic’
-- B y   M a r g a r e t   T a l e v
-- 2012-09-04T13:14:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/obama-s-convention-speech-to-be-aspirational-pragmatic-.html
Aides to President Barack Obama’s
re-election campaign said today that his speech to the
Democratic National Convention in Charlotte, North Carolina,
this week will be “aspirational” and “pragmatic.”  Deputy Campaign Manager  Stephanie Cutter  and other campaign
aides speaking at a Bloomberg Breakfast in Charlotte also said
the president’s speech accepting his party’s nomination for re-
election will be detailed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Margaret Talev in Washington at 
 mtalev@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
